HEADWORD: Decerption
<hw>De*cerp"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of plucking off; a cropping.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is plucked off or rent away; a fragment;
a piece.</def> <rj><au>Glanvill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decertation</ent>⟦br⟧
